<br>
summoning an epic and fully equiping the pet 3.8 hp/mana ratio thats if all spec checks fail and no focus gear for mana pres. <br>
so with summoning efficiency 3 and spec conjuration maxed and scm3 (assuming it still works) <br>
the epic pet is at 340 mana or so. <br>
set of plate mail down around 225 mana. <br>
muzzle at 80 mana <br>
burnout 150 <br>
<br>
total mana 795 <br>
still assuming 4k hp. <br>
now were around 5hp/mana spent. <br>
<br>
chain casting gvoc earth. spec'd conj/scm3/ summoning efficiency 3: no thurg/ss/kael robe or pants<br>
pet 275<br>
burnout 4/5 =150<br>
<br>
for a total cost of 425 mana<br>
<br>
gvoc earth weighs in around 3500 hp. <br>
for a hp to mana ratio of 8.25 <br>
<br>
now tell me how asking for a 3.25 ratio heal is close to asking for it to be anywhere near as efficient as chain casting. you cant tell me that plate and muzzle of mardu doubles the pets effective hp. <br>
tests of gvoc earth against lvl 44ish gnolls in jaggedpine. with out plate pet walks out of fight with 2 bubs of health left. with plate he walks out with around 3. roughly an increase of 33% against melee weak opponents. muzzle of mardu is 11 % haste. <br>
<br>
in fungus grove against shrooms the plate makes means that gvoc earth will survive a solo fight against a shroom where as no plate and the shroom is turning to run as soon as the pet dies. ( no nuking used till end of fight). <br>
tougher oppenent only 15 to 20% increase in pet power from plate. <br>
<br>
sending only the pet against lvl 57 giants in kael, summoned plate results in the pet lasting about 3 seconds longer. or a who cares increase in pet power. <br>
<br>
so if i dont nuke a shroom and i summon him plate and muzzle:<br>
if i use the current 52 pet heal i'll spend 1375 mana healing the pet. if i just summon a new pet muzzle and plate. i'll use 900 or so mana ( minus whatever little i'll get back reclaiming the pet). <br>
if i had just chain cast pets at the shroom with no muzzle or plate i'd have spent 425 mana or so. since the second pet walks out at nearly full health. <br>
<br>
now requesting a 3.25 ratio heal as the lvl 52 60 and 65 heals ( no lvl 65 heal planned so far) hte lvl 52 heal would wind up healing 893 hp. or 25% of gvoc earth. so 3 heals would add ~2700 hp. at a cost of 825 mana still far less efficient than chain casting pets. however it does come close to summoning a completely new pet and all of its gear.<br>
<br>
Now given that chain casting has some drawbacks. you having to time the casts and type /pet back off, possibly get summoned if timed incorrectly, pet takes a couple of seconds to reestablish agro ( ooooooo dificult) and healing the pet does not ( other than currently being rediculously mana inefficient) i think the 2x better ratio for chain casting vs a 3.25 ratio heal is justified. however the current 4x better ratio of chaining is unwarrented. <br>
<br>
recommended modifications to current spells<br>
52 heal 275 mana for 800 hp. 2.9 ratio<br>
60 heal 400 mana for 1250 hp. 3.1 ratio<br>
recommended added spells<br>
65 heal 550 mana for 1800 hp. 3.27 ratio 12 sec cast 12 sec recast.<br>
a pet only celestial elixer would work also i guess.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
quote and answer time<br>
sirrilen: Keeping one pet also means you don't get summoned, which again is huge for bigger mobs.<br>
Answer: currently you get a 4x better ratio for assuming that risk. <br>
<br>
sirrillen: Say pets are 3 times as strong roughly when fully buffed. If you have have to chain cast 7 pets the first one is very effective and the others are trash. (Even if you somehow chain casted the epic, it would pop without it's damage shield.) <br>
Answer: id put it closer to 2x vs a completely unbuffed pet. even chain casting i still cast burnout and sometimes ds the pet. plate and muzzle would add an additional 20-30% effectiveness over not having them. <br>
<br>
sirrillen: So don't argue it on the merit that is supposed to be &quot;exactly the same as summoning and buffing a new pet.&quot; Its not.<br>
Answer: i didnt argue it that it would be exactly the same as summoning and rebuffing the pet in fact i still beleive that it should cost more. however it should be close. to comepletely heal an epic pet from 1hp will take<br>
7 casts of the 52 heal in its current form. that equals 1925 mana no spec/focus to completely resummon an epic and gear it up takes 1050 mana. using the 60 heal its 1600 mana and you wait a little while the pet regens the last 400ish hp.<br>
<br>
<br>
Raz :If the purpose of the heal is to save your pet from death, then in order to be better at saving your pet than a nuke, it has be be a near-substitute for mend companion or complete heal<br>
Answer: why does it have to be a complete heal to save my pet from death a 25% (1000ish hp for epic) or 50% ( 2000ish for epic) heal would equally save my pet. and not infring on other others domains. i dont want a complete heal ( well not true) but i'd be happy with a decent powerfull heal in the 1500-1800 hp range at 65. or at the very least a dowtime reducer that approaches destroying and resummoning/equipping a nearly dead pet. sitting for 10 minutes while my pet heals or because i blew half of my mana healing it is annoying.<br>
<br>
sirrllen and raz: (paraphrased) big pet heals will devalue mend companion<br>
Answer: call me strange but a manaless instant 3000 hp heal is never useless. especially to a pet cleric. <br>
<br>
One last proposal if /pet sit down tripled the pets regen rate all of this would be pretty moot. since verant is probably reluctant to give us a good combat heal and the chain summoning folks dont seem to want anything other than chainsummoning to be efficient. <br>
<br>
ps. if a spell requires the use of a star ruby to cast it wont be used. as a wizard when the last time he disintegrated anything was and that only requires an opal. <br>
<br>
<br>
Tezron<br>
