a mob that doubles for 250 every 3 seconds. will be doing 166 dps. how long is your pet going to last against such a mob? <br>
about 24 seconds. now a 300 hp per tick HOT heals 50 dps. <br>
making the above mob's dps now 116. now that pet will survive 35 seconds. <br>
<br>
now lets talk about <br>
using your mana regen numbers sitting on a horse ( for always med) using mc3 (3)kei(17) ft3(3) and transons(3) 26 from spells and another 24 or so from sitting.  your regenning around 50 mana per tick total.  thats 5 ticks to regen elemental infusion at 250 per cast.  you are healing 17.5 hp/sec doing nothing but casting transon's as soon as you regen the mana. <br>
<br>
now lets look at summoning new pets. at 300 mana per pet. its 6 ticks for a new pet. or 36 seconds. converting gvoc earths hp's to mana you are summoing 97 hp/second chaincasting pets as soon as the mana is available. <br>
<br>
so what do these numbers tell us. that a mage with kei ft3 mc3 transons sitting on a horse can infinitly tank any mob that doubles for 78 or less every 3 seconds. but a mage that is healing thier pet can only heal a pet infinitly if the monster doubles for 27 or less every 3 seconds. or 3 times more efficient to summon a new pet vs healing the old one with current spells. in an infiite senario. <br>
now lets consider a 300 hp per tick hot at around 350 mana. <br>
7 ticks to regen the mana. that would move our sustained tanking to a mob that doubles for 54 every 3 seconds. <br>
<br>
this is an infinite senario assuming the mob has unlimited hp and never dies and your pet and you never should lose any hp or mana. <br>
<br>
