<br>
<br>
lets try closer to reality senario. say a 150 max quadding mob every 4 seconds. lets say its average hit on the pet is 120 and 3 of 4 swings land. this puts the mob at 90 dps. and lets give that mob 8000 hp. and say the epic pet fully buffed puts out 60 dps and has 4000 hp. and that the mob does not regen or heal itself.<br>
<br>
 it will take the epic pet 133 seconds or 22 ticks to kill this mob. <br>
the mob will have done 12000 dmg to the pet. if you sustain the epic pet on this mob you will have to cast a 1500 4tick hot 6 times fo 2100 mana. you will also have had to cast 4 infusions since the pet would die 100 seconds into the fight without them for an additional 920 mana .  you will have regened 1100 mana ( assuming all the same buffs/aa's) during this fight for a net loss of 2000m. your downtime will be 4 minutes after this fight to recover your mana + whatever time it takes for your pet to heal . <br>
<br>
now lets look at chain casting pets. in the same senario. <br>
for the sake of this test we will assume you are not bothering to buff the pet at all and just sending them to thier death. <br>
lets give gvoc earth 25dps unbuffed so we are looking at 320 seconds (54 ticks) to kill the same mob. the mob will put out 29000 damage during this time. you will need to cast 8 additional pets to kill it, one every 35 seconds. for a total expenditure of 2560 mana during this time you will have regened 2700 mana with the same buffs. for a net gain of 140 mana. your downtime 0 minutes. <br>
<br>
now lets add burnout 3 as a right click on the pants and convert gvoc earth to 38 dps. now the fight lasts 210 seconds (35 ticks). the mob did 19000 damage. you need 5 additional pets. mana expenditure 1600. mana gained 1750. net gain 150 mana. <br>
<br>
ok now lets try healing gvoc earth with the 1500 hp hot. <br>
it will still take 210 seconds to kill the mob. 87 seconds into fight gvoc earth would die without infusion to back this up. <br>
9 casts of hot 13500 hp for 3150 mana<br>
4 casts of infusion.  2320 hp for 920 mana<br>
total mana expenditure 4070 mana<br>
