Level: 65<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2037<br> <font color=#333333>(10/5/02 12:09:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Heal? How about the ones we have</span><hr size=1> I am getting pretty tired of being accused of being anti-mage, when in fact I am a dedicated and successful champion of the mage class.<br>
<br>
Remember the pet upgrades from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The Great Patch</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?  These were:<br>
<br>
1) Neutral Faction Pets<br>
2) Stronger Pets<br>
3) Removing Pet Experience Penalty<br>
<br>
Did these happen by accident?  No, they took a concerted effort by the mage community to voice their concerns, propose remedies, and present arguments in favor of those remedies.  My part in all this was, since I am a professional writer, to gather and summarize <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>all</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the various opinions about what mage problems were and how to remedy them, to compare the various proposed remedies, and to summarize the best arguments and counter arguments for each proposed solution.<br>
<br>
First, I classified and summarized the major schools of thought on how to improve the mage class:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=42.topic">Step 1: How to categorize class balance issues?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=71.topic">Classifying Proposed Remedies to Magician Class Balance</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
I slogged through dozens of threads and hundreds of posts to extract those ideas that were repeated by multiple mages and which seemed to enjoy at least some support <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>regardless of whether I agreed or not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.<br>
<br>
At the time, the general consensus was that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> considered mages to be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>overpowered</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, and that therefore, no significant remedies would be forthcoming.  Thus there was a great burden on the mage community to express our ideas clearly with persuasive arguments in favor of our proposals.<br>
<br>
One popular school of thought said that pets needed to be made stronger.  Although I had a different agenda, I still summarized and compared all the various method for making pets stronger:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=82.topic">Increased Pet Strength, Summary Pro and Con</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Notice this includes arguments for <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>and</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> against increasing pet strength.<br>
<br>
Another school of thought was that the penalties that mages paid for having pets were entirely too much for the benefit gained:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=90.topic">Petition: Reduce Pet Penalties?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
There were also many outstanding bugs which effects mages, which I gathered in:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=86.topic">LIST: Bugs, flaws, and minor fixes</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
At the time, I was of the opinion that pets were likely already strong enough, and that most pet penalties were probably justified, but that the central problem was that because of bad pathing, pets were unusable in entirely too many places.  Make our pets available everywhere, I reasoned, and mages would be powerful enough.<br>
<br>
First I argued that bad pathing was the responsibility of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and not the responsibility of mages to deal with the consequences of a serious design flaw:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=97.topic">REQUEST: Reduce Pathing Costs</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> maintained in response that first, bad pathing could not be fixed except an enormous expense, and second, that there was really hardly any bad pathing at all.  I collected a list of places where pets were not allowed due to bad pathing:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=85.topic">LIST: Where are Pets Not Allowed?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Looking at the various proposed solutions, I concluded that making pets neutral faction would eliminate most of the risk of having pets near bad pathing, and would take little programming effort.  However, this was a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>radical</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> change to game mechanics, and would have profound effects for every mage in every zone.  Almost everyone agreed that that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would never do such a thing, and that neutral pets were probably abuseable.  So I posted to several forums including this one inviting players to come up with ways that neutral faction pets could be abused:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessage?topicID=63.topic">Brainstorm: List Consequences of Indifferent Pets</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
What was the result of all this?  Pets were made stronger, the pet experience penalty was removed, and pets were made neutral faction.<br>
<br>
None of this was <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>accomplished</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> by crying <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;gimmee gimmee&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and seeking the most powerful upgrades, but analyzing various alternatives and putting forth the best arguments on their behalf, as well as countering the counter arguments.<br>
<br>
Mages are now more powerful than they have been at any time since before <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Kunark</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I am sure I am not alone in being suspicious of asking for any major upgrade for mages beyond that.<br>
<br>
Giving mages <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Root</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is one example of an extraordinarily powerful upgrade, a pet heal that was too good would likewise be a powerful upgrade.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, mages are no longer in need of powerful upgrades.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uylaine76.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1078<br> <font color=#333333>(10/5/02 5:37:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Heal? How about the ones we have</span><hr size=1> I think you've done a good job <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I didnt agree with some of your suggestions before, but still a decent job<br>
<br>
I dont really know if we *need* another pet heal.  I mean, honestly, the only time I use heals are in emergencies or I dont feel like doing much.  You can solo much much better not healing pet at all and having improved reclaim<br>
<br>
Just resummon pet <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It'll always be more efficient than heals unless we get a complete heal which i dont think will happen <p><a href="http://www.bladesofwrath.com">
