<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60178">Archmage Ylaine</a>
<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=280818">High Priestess Daemoness</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucalebe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 395<br> <font color=#333333>(10/5/02 7:35:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Heal</span><hr size=1> Not a complete heal Ylaine, but a lot more effiecent heal.<br>
<br>
A big difference between the 2 actually.<br>
<br>
What many are advocating is a heal that makes healing a pet as valuable as chaining a pet. <br>
<br>
The more you lavish on a pet, the more incentive you have to keep it alive, even if it means you expend more mana doing it, AND lose the ability to chain pets when the mob is dead to &quot;fill up&quot; your mana bar.<br>
<br>
So there are a few draw backs, but the increase in pet power by equiping your pet, and maybe getting it buffed for plat/focus items is worth it to some, especially if you have the epic pet.<br>
<br>
The lack of a &quot;GOOD&quot; heal, makes a soloing magician with an epic pet have to choose not to buff it, or add weapons to it, as you will chain GV pets as soon as it dies, because healing really isn't an option if you want to take on harder mobs. Chaining pets is the only real choice you have.<br>
<br>
Those against a better heal have said it clearly that they don't want a seconds viable option to the very powerful ability of chaining pets.<br>
<br>
I and many DISAGREE and want that option, the same way a necro has gotten a better heal and that new option. Remember when it comes to soloing power, a necro with SO MANY escape spells as well as soloing tools from FD/FEAR/Runes/DARKNESS/ROOT/ and the same 3 options we have. PET/RUN/GATE , now the necro arsenal contains a very good and effiecent pet heal.<br>
<br>
I would like the magician class to have that same option they do. HEAL the pet effeicenly. <br>
<br>
People say prove WHY you need it, as you can chain pets.<br>
<br>
When a lot people say You can not chain epic pets effectively, and also like to lavish weapons/armour etc.. on a pet to make it that more powerful.<br>
<br>
It seems they gloss it over, as unimportant, because they don't like the idea that something would be as good as chaining a pet.<br>
<br>
It still boogles my mind. They lose nothing, some of us game a new option. What the hell is wrong with that. <br>
<br>
I am done trying to convince people who DON'T want a new heal spell, who's only point is that we can chain pets, it is a very powerful ability. So ANYTHING else is not needed. To them it may not be, to me it is.<br>
<br>
The entire discussion trying to convince some is mute anyway, as shown in the one suggestion on a different thread dealing with a new heal spell, requiring a Star Ruby. <br>
<br>
That alone should tell any and all who read these threads that some are not seriously considering a new heal spell.<br>
<br>
So what happens is a suggestion is made for a new heal spell but with a cost that makes it such a joke, no one would ever mem it or use it over chaining pets. <br>
<br>
Calebe <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showMessageRange?topicID=65.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showMessageRange?topicID=65.topic&start=41&stop=57>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showPrevMessage?topicID=65.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showNextMessage?topicID=65.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.threadControl?topicID=65.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=65.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=65.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="the